<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph box="[4,914,285,656]" pageId="25" pageNumber="278" type="mainText">
Annual herb. Leaves alternate, fleshy. Flowers solitary, subtended by 2 leaf-like bracteoles; perianth lobes 5, united at the very base, unequal and winged above the middle in fruit; wing falling off along a definite line of dehiscence and leaving behind a 2-lobed protuberance; stamens 5; anthers appendiculate; stigmas 2, subulate. One sp., 
<taxonomicName authority="Bunge" authorityName="Bunge" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Rhaphidophyton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="25" pageNumber="278" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="turkestana">R. turkestana Bunge</taxonomicName>
, Transcaspian lowlands.
</paragraph>
